{"title_page": "Lig\u0119za", "text_new": "[[File:Miko\u0142aj Spytek Lig\u0119za.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Miko\u0142aj Spytek Lig\u0119za]]\n[[File:Szostak1626.png|thumb|200px|right|\"Sz\u00f3stak\" (coin) with King [[Sigismund III Vasa]] and the coat of arms of Treasurer Hermolaus Lig\u0119za (1626)]]\n[[File:Lig\u0119za mausoleum, Bernardine church, Rzesz\u00f3w.jpg|thumb|200px|right|[http://www.rzeszow.pl/miasto-rzeszow/historia/zabytki-rzeszowa/architektura-sakralna/dziela-wybitnych-mistrzow-w-bazylice-oo-bernardynow-w-rzeszowie/ Lig\u0119za mausoleum], [http://www.bernardyni.rzeszow.pl/ Bernardine Church], Rzesz\u00f3w]]\nThe '''Lig\u0119za''', plural: '''Lig\u0119zowie''' was a [[Poland|Polish]] [[szlachta|noble family]]. <ref name=\"grocholski\">{{cite web|url=http://genealogia.grocholski.pl/gd/rodzina.php?id=04747|title=Genealogia dynastyczna|author=Ryszard Jurzak|publisher=genealogia.grocholski.pl|accessdate=2014-01-27}}</ref> The family became important in the 15th and 16th century. <ref>https://polona.pl/search/?query=Lig%C4%99za&filters=public:1</ref>\n\n==Notable members==\n\n*[[Dzier\u017cykraj P\u00f3\u0142kozic]], [[castellan]] of [[Po\u0142aniec]]\n*[[Jan Lig\u0119za]] <ref>https://www.ipsb.nina.gov.pl/a/biografia/jan-ligeza-h-polkozic-zm-1419-wojewoda-leczycki-starosta-leczycki</ref> (died 1419), [[voivode]] of [[\u0141\u0119czyca Voivodeship|\u0141\u0119czyca]], commander of the 32nd [[Chor\u0105giew (military unit)|Banner]] at the [[Battle of Grunwald]]\n*[[Hermolaus Lig\u0119za]] <ref>https://www.ipsb.nina.gov.pl/a/biografia/hermolaus-ligeza-z-bobrku-h-polkozic</ref> (died 1632), [[marszalek|marshal]] of the [[Crown Tribunal]], [[podskarbi|Grand Treasurer of the Crown]]\n*[[Feliks Lig\u0119za]] <ref>http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bligeza.html</ref> (c. 1500 \u2013 1560), [[archbishop]] of [[Lw\u00f3w]]\n*[[Konstancja Lig\u0119za]] (died 1648), married Prince [[Jerzy Sebastian Lubomirski]]\n*{{Interlanguage link multi|Miko\u0142aj Lig\u0119za|pl|3=Miko\u0142aj Lig\u0119za (ok. 1530 \u2013 1603)}} <ref>https://www.ipsb.nina.gov.pl/a/biografia/mikolaj-ligeza-z-bobrku-h-polkozic</ref> (c. 1530 \u2013 1603), [[castellan]] of [[Czech\u00f3w, \u015awi\u0119tokrzyskie Voivodeship|Czech\u00f3w]]\n*[[Miko\u0142aj Spytek Lig\u0119za]] (c. 1562 \u2013 1637), owner of the City of [[Rzesz\u00f3w]] <ref>http://www.rzeszow.pl/miasto-rzeszow/historia/historia-rzeszowa</ref> <ref>http://www.rzeszow.pl/miasto-rzeszow/historia/rzeszowskie-historie-i-historyjki/mikolaj-spytek-ligeza-z-bobrku-herbu-polkozic</ref>\n*[[Stanis\u0142aw Lig\u0119za z Gorzyc]] (died 1462), [[knight]]\n*[[Stanis\u0142aw Szcz\u0119sny Lig\u0119za]] (died 1536), [[castellan]] of [[Che\u0142mno]]\n\n==Coat of arms==\nThe family used the [[P\u00f3\u0142kozic coat of arms]].\n\n<gallery widths=200 heights=200 align=center>\nPOL COA P\u00f3\u0142kozic.svg\n</gallery>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*Adam Boniecki: Herbarz polski. T. 14. Warszawa: Sk\u0142ad G\u0142\u00f3wny Gebethner i Wolff, 1911, pp. 249-258. <ref>https://crispa.uw.edu.pl/object/files/416454/display/PDF</ref>\n*Mariusz Lubczy\u0144ski: Pocz\u0105tki rodziny Lig\u0119z\u00f3w herbu P\u00f3\u0142kozic. Pozna\u0144: Towarzystwo Mi\u0142osnik\u00f3w Historii w Poznaniu ; Pozna\u0144skie Towarzystwo Przyjaci\u00f3\u0142 Nauk, 1999, pp. 1-26. <ref>https://www.wbc.poznan.pl/dlibra/publication/517161/edition/425918/content</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:House of Ligeza}}\n[[Category:Lig\u0119za| ]]\n\n\n{{Poland-noble-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:Miko\u0142aj Spytek Lig\u0119za.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Miko\u0142aj Spytek Lig\u0119za]]\n[[File:Szostak1626.png|thumb|200px|right|\"Sz\u00f3stak\" (coin) with King [[Sigismund III Vasa]] and the coat of arms of Treasurer Hermolaus Lig\u0119za (1626)]]\n[[File:Lig\u0119za mausoleum, Bernardine church, Rzesz\u00f3w.jpg|thumb|200px|right|[http://www.rzeszow.pl/miasto-rzeszow/historia/zabytki-rzeszowa/architektura-sakralna/dziela-wy